#Usage:
#-----------------------------------------------
video screenrecord # Starts interactive screen recording
video screenrecord --help # Shows this help message

#Video Options:
#----------------
mp4 (default), mkv

#Audio Options:
#---------------------------------------------------
    At start, you will be asked:
    1 = No audio
    2 = System audio (PulseAudio)
    3 = Microphone (e.g. default: ALSA/Pulse input)
    4 = Both (system & microphone mixed)

    If multiple microphones are detected, you'll be asked to choose one

#Dependencies:
#---------------------------------------------
ffmpeg, xdotool, xrandr, x11-utils, pulseaudio

#Recording:
#----------------------------------------------------------
    Automatically detects which monitor your terminal is on

    Records the full screen of that monitor

    Saves the video to: ~/data/Videos/screencast_YYYY-MM-DD_HH-MM-SS.mkv

    Stop the recording by pressing [ENTER]

